## 8. gstack â€” Development Workflow Skills

[gstack](https://github.com/garrytan/gstack) is a suite of 25 specialized Claude Code skills that provide distinct cognitive modes for each phase of development â€” ideation, planning, design, reviewing, shipping, QA, debugging, deployment, and more. Each skill acts as a specialist rather than a generic assistant.

**Important:** These are 25 separate skills invoked individually, not one `/gstack` command.

### Planning & Ideation

| Skill | Role | What it does |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `/office-hours` | YC partner | Brainstorming â€” forcing questions for startups or design thinking for builders |
| `/plan-ceo-review` | Founder / product thinker | Challenge assumptions, find the 10-star version of the plan |
| `/plan-eng-review` | Engineering manager | Lock architecture, review edge cases, validate data flow |
| `/plan-design-review` | Designer | Rate design dimensions 0-10, fix the plan to reach 10 |

### Design

| Skill | Role | What it does |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `/design-consultation` | Design systems lead | Create a complete design system (DESIGN.md) with typography, color, layout |
| `/design-review` | Visual QA designer | Find and fix visual inconsistencies, spacing issues, AI slop patterns |

### Implementation & Debugging

| Skill | Role | What it does |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `/investigate` | Root cause analyst | Systematic debugging â€” investigate, analyze, hypothesize, implement |
| `/browse` | Browser automation | Headless browser for navigating, clicking, screenshots, form testing |
| `/freeze` | Scope limiter | Restrict file edits to a specific directory for the session |
| `/unfreeze` | Scope restorer | Clear the freeze boundary, allow edits everywhere again |
| `/careful` | Safety guard | Warn before destructive commands (rm -rf, DROP TABLE, force-push) |
| `/guard` | Full safety mode | Combines `/careful` + `/freeze` for maximum safety |

### Testing & QA

| Skill | Role | What it does |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `/qa` | QA lead | Systematic QA testing â€” find bugs, fix them, verify fixes |
| `/qa-only` | QA reporter | Report-only QA â€” structured bug report without fixing anything |
| `/benchmark` | Performance engineer | Performance regression detection with Core Web Vitals baselines |
| `/setup-browser-cookies` | Session manager | Import browser cookies for authenticated `/browse` and `/qa` sessions |

### Review & Shipping

| Skill | Role | What it does |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `/review` | Paranoid code reviewer | Pre-landing code review focused on production failure modes |
| `/codex` | Second opinion | OpenAI Codex wrapper â€” independent code review, adversarial challenge, or consult |
| `/ship` | Release engineer | Run tests, create PR, deploy â€” one-command shipping |
| `/land-and-deploy` | Deploy engineer | Merge PR, wait for CI, verify production health via canary checks |
| `/setup-deploy` | Deploy configurator | Configure deployment settings (platform, URL, health checks) for `/land-and-deploy` |
| `/canary` | Post-deploy monitor | Watch live app for errors, perf regressions, and page failures after deploy |

### Maintenance

| Skill | Role | What it does |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `/document-release` | Technical writer | Post-ship docs update â€” sync README, CHANGELOG, ARCHITECTURE with what shipped |
| `/retro` | Team lead | Sprint/task retrospective with per-person feedback and trend tracking |
| `/gstack-upgrade` | Updater | Upgrade gstack to the latest version |

**Browsing rule:** Use `/browse` for **all web browsing**. Never use `mcp__claude-in-chrome__*` tools.

**Troubleshooting:** If gstack skills aren't working, run `cd .claude/skills/gstack && ./setup` to rebuild.

## 9. Workflow

Follow this workflow for all significant work:

1. **Plan** â€” Enter plan mode, define approach
2. **CEO Review** â€” `/plan-ceo-review` â€” Challenge assumptions, find the 10-star version
3. **Eng Review** â€” `/plan-eng-review` â€” Lock architecture, edge cases, data flow
4. **Implement** â€” Write code following the plan
5. **Verify** â€” `/verify` â€” Run automated checks
6. **Review** â€” `/review` â€” Pre-landing code review
7. **Ship** â€” `/ship` â€” Tests, PR, deploy
